-- Poland's Q1 GDP growth seen at 3.0 pct-FinMin's economist
-- By Pawel Sobczak
-- Tue May 13, 2014 06:00AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, May 13 (Reuters) - Poland's economic growth is likely to have accelerated to 3.0 percent in the first quarter of 2014 from 2.7 percent in the previous three month period, the Finance Ministry's chief economist, Ludwik Kotecki, said on Tuesday.

"I expect that GDP growth will amount to three percent," Kotecki told Reuters.